{
  "texts": [
    "It aims to search for hidden patterns or relationships in the data (Attri et al, 2023).",
    "Semi-supervised learning arises when some data is labeled, like in supervised learning, while some data is unlabeled, like in unsupervised learning (Engelen and Hoos, 2020).",
    "Distinguishing between classification and regression tasks in ML is also crucial because they produce different output data types.",
    "Classification tasks seek qualitative results and organize inputs into classes.",
    "One use of the classification is categorizing plant leaf diseases into distinct groups (Shoaib et al., 2022)."
  ]
}